Subject: Drop obsolete Meson x11 option for mutter 50+

Newer mutter releases build the X11 code unconditionally and no longer expose a
Meson `x11` option. Ubuntu's packaging still passes `-Dx11=true`, which now
causes `meson setup` to fail with:

  ERROR: Unknown option: "x11"

Remove the obsolete flag so the package builds again on updated Ubuntu 26.04
sources while preserving the rest of the distro packaging.

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -24,4 +24,3 @@
 	-Dauto_features=enabled \
 	-Degl_device=true \
 	-Dremote_desktop=true \
-	-Dwayland_eglstream=true \
-	-Dx11=true
+	-Dwayland_eglstream=true
